The paper proposes a neural network model that learns to represent and execute programs, which is a topic related to artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The model is recurrent and compositional, which suggests it may also be relevant to machine learning (cs.LG) and natural language processing (cs.CL). The model is also domain-specific and operates in multiple perceptually diverse environments, which could be related to computer vision (cs.CV). Finally, the paper mentions the use of a scratch pad with read-write pointers to cache intermediate results of computation, which suggests a potential connection to neural networks (cs.NE).
